                         SUMMARY                                  9231 1451
                                                                  9231 1451
  MOD 2 incorporates a complete revision of most of the data in   9231 1451
the 236U evaluation. No changes were made to the resolved         9231 1451
resonance parameters. A minor revision was made to the            9231 1451
unresolved resonance parameters to enhance agreement with         9231 1451
experimental data and for greater compatibility with the smooth   9231 1451
cross sections. Above the unresolved resonance region (En=100     9231 1451
keV), new evaluations were performed of the neutron total,        9231 1451
elastic, (n,n'), (n,2n), (n,3n), (n,4n), (n,f), (n,nf), (n,2nf),  9231 1451
(n,3nf), (n,4nf), and (n,gamma) cross sections, as well as their  9231 1451
associated angular and energy distributions. Additionally,        9231 1451
prompt fission nubar was revised using experimental data          9231 1451
normalized to ENDF/B-VI standards. The energy range of the        9231 1451
evaluation was increased from 20 to 30 MeV.                       9231 1451
