                  THEORETICAL ANALYSIS                            9231 1451
                                                                  9231 1451
   To provide the new data, coupled channel optical model calcu-  9231 1451
lations were performed with the ECIS96 code for the lowest 5      9231 1451
members of the U236 ground state rotational band. The optical     9231 1451
model potential (Yo92) is available from the RIPL-2 OMP library   9231 1451
as RIPL-2 potential number 5.  These calculations were used to    9231 1451
provide elastic and inelastic cross sections and angular          9231 1451
distributions for discrete states of 236U, as well as the         9231 1451
neutron total cross section.  Similar calculations coupling 3     9231 1451
states were used to provide neutron transmission coefficients     9231 1451
for nuclear reaction theory calculations with the GNASH           9231 1451
(Ch01,Yo98) Hauser- Feshbach statistical/fission/preequilibrium   9231 1451
code. The evaluated (n,f) cross section was obtained from         9231 1451
experimental data; the fission barrier parameters in the GNASH    9231 1451
calculations were adjusted to agree with the evaluation to        9231 1451
within a few percent.  The GNASH calculations were used directly  9231 1451
for the MF=3 cross sections and correlated energy-angle spectra   9231 1451
in MF=6 for the (n,n'continuum), (n,2n), (n,3n), and (n,4n)       9231 1451
reactions.  The calculations were also used in combination with   9231 1451
experimental data to determine the (n,gamma) cross section.       9231 1451
